= xdebug_start_code_coverage
Starts code coverage
void
[int options]
FUNC_CODE_COVERAGE

TXT:
This function starts gathering the information for code coverage. The
information that is collected consists of an two dimensional array with as
primairy index the executed filename and as secondary key the line number. The
value in the elements represents the total number of execution units on this
line have been executed.

TXT:
Options to this function are:

XDEBUG_CC_UNUSED
Enables scanning of code to figure out which line has executable code.
XDEBUG_CC_DEAD_CODE
Enables branch analyzes to figure out whether code can be executed.
